  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd   \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cessation of egg delivery",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The All Sri Lanka Poultry Traders Association has announced a nationwide suspension of egg distribution in protest against the imposition of a maximum retail price for eggs.",
        "Ajith Gunasekara, president of the association, pointed out that due to the increase in the cost of production, it is not possible to distribute the eggs in the plantation.",
        "The maximum retail price of a white egg has been fixed at Rs 43 and the maximum retail price of a brown egg has been fixed at Rs 45 with effect from midnight on Friday (19) and a special gazette notification has been issued.",
        "In this case, a meeting between the All Sri Lankan Poultry Traders Association and the Minister of Commerce, Trade and Food Safety Nalin Fernando will be held at the Ministry of Trade and Food Safety tomorrow (22)."
      ],
